# 2. しゅわしゅわとモヤモヤ

Ichika: I'm sorry about not allowing us to give a quick response. I know you're all really excited about this collaboration...
Saki: No, don't apologize!
Saki: Mr. Shindo even said that we shouldn't go ahead until we're all on the same page!
Honami: Right. This collaboration isn't all that's involved. This matter is going to affect how we do things moving forward.
Honami: That being said...
Honami: Do you know why you're so bothered by this, Ichika?
Ichika: That's the thing. I'm not really sure myself...
Ichika: But I keep getting this weird feeling.
Honami: I see... I wish I could help you somehow...
Shiho: In any case, let's take our time with this since we still have plenty of time to think.
Saki: Yeah! Slow and steady!
Saki: Plus, we're having that party in SEKAI to mark our debut song becoming a big success♪
Saki: So, let's celebrate first, and then think this through!
Ichika: Oh, right... I forgot that we were having that party today.
Honami: Hehe. Since it's our big event, why don't we go buy some snacks for it?
Shiho: Sounds good. Actually, if we don't, they're probably going to ask us why we didn't bring any.
Ichika: Hehe. Right. I can see it already.
Saki: Haha♪ Then, let's go grab some snacks and head over to see Miku and the others!
Ichika: Okay!
Miku: Are we all ready?
Rin & Saki: Yup!
KAITO: Ready...
MEIKO: Then, here's to your debut song becoming a big hit... Raise your glasses!
MEIKO: Cheers!
Everyone: Cheers!
Luka: Congratulations, girls.
Rin: How awesome is it that your very first song went so viral?!
Ichika: To be fair, Miku's version is the one that went viral.
Shiho: Still, I'm glad that so many people decided to listen to our performance...
Saki: Me too! A bunch of people even posted videos of themselves singing our song after listening to the Miku version!
Saki: Remember the ones who said it was really fun to sing because the music and our performance were so good? That made me super happy!
Honami: Hehe. Me too.
Honami: You and Ichika really did come up with a wonderful song, Saki. Thank you both for putting so much effort into it.
Saki: Hehe. You and Shiho looked so cool while playing it!
Shiho: Thanks. I guess all our pair practice paid off.
Len: Hm?
Len: Hey, is anyone else seeing these sodas for the first time?
Rin: Yeah, I was gonna ask the same thing! What's with all these flavors?!
Saki: Oh, about those. The company that makes them asked us to appear in one of their commercials!
Len: Huh? One of their commercials?
Ichika: Yeah, which is why we thought we could try some of their products together.
Len: Huh... Still, this is a huge lineup.
Saki: I like all these flavors, but I recommend the melon soda the most♪ Making ice cream floats with this is always fun because it ends up tasting just like the ones you can get at cafes and stuff!
Rin: Wow, that sounds delicious! I wanna make that☆
Luka: Still, it's incredible how you received this sort of offer just following the release of your debut song.
Shiho: A part of me feels that things are going a little too well for us at the moment. Also, we haven't actually agreed to take their offer yet.
Miku: Wait, why not?
Ichika: Because I'm still unsure...
Luka: You are?
Ichika: *Nod*
Len: Any reason as to why?
Ichika: Any reason? I'm still having trouble putting it into words...
Ichika: But the thing is...
Luka: I see...
Luka: They want Leo/need to make a VIRTUAL SINGER version of each song you produce moving forward...?
Ichika: *Nod*
Ichika: I don't have a problem with you singing instead of me, Miku. We've already been having you sing our songs up until now.
Ichika: Having you sing songs before they're finalized has been really helpful too.
Ichika: But a part of me feels uncomfortable with the idea of making you this integral part of our promotional strategy...
Miku: Ichika...
Honami: You've meant quite a lot to Ichika since she was little, so I don't think she wants to treat you unfairly in any way...
Shiho: You're also the reason why we decided to form our band in elementary school.
Len: In elementary school...
Len: Come to think of it, Ichika, what were you like back then?
Ichika: Huh? M-Me...?
Len: Yeah, it's never really come up before.
Len: But now I'm curious. And talking about it could provide you with a hint to solving this problem, right?
Ichika: A hint...
Ichika: Right. Standing still like this is only going to cause everyone else around me trouble...
Ichika: This is going to be a little embarrassing for me, but...
Ichika: I discovered Miku when I was in fifth grade. I remember going to the park with my family and...
